## 1. Energy & Chemicals Backbone (2025–2029)

- **Marcellus-to-Houston Gas Pipeline + Pennsylvania Chemicals Hub**  
  *What*: 1.5B cubic feet/day pipeline, $200B chemical hub (plastics, fertilizers).  
  *Where*: Marcellus Shale (PA/WV) to Houston, TX; chemical hub near Pittsburgh, PA.  
  *When*: 2025-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $15B  
  *Impact*: Cuts flaring 50% ($5B co-op revenue), feeds Houston LNG ($1.5T exports), powers 2GW reactors.

- **Permian-to-Houston Gas Pipeline**  
  *What*: 500M cubic feet/day pipeline tapping stranded gas.  
  *Where*: Permian Basin (TX/NM) to Houston, TX.  
  *When*: 2027-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $5B  
  *Impact*: $1.5B/year revenue, fuels $500B Houston chemicals, supports ICE/gas-hybrids ($400B sales).

- **Marcellus-to-Chicago Gas Pipeline**  
  *What*: 1B cubic feet/day pipeline.  
  *Where*: Marcellus Shale (PA/WV) to Chicago, IL.  
  *When*: 2025-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $10B  
  *Impact*: Supplies 2GW reactor/upgrader ($3B revenue), Midwest co-ops ($5B trade), cuts flaring ($1B savings).

- **Payette Gas Fields Pipeline**  
  *What*: 1B cubic feet/day pipeline.  
  *Where*: Payette Basin (ID/WY) to Chicago, IL, and Houston, TX (split terminus).  
  *When*: 2026-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $3B  
  *Impact*: Links 1GW reactor to hubs ($200B exports), rural co-ops ($1B revenue).

- **Houston Co-op Upgrader**  
  *What*: 100K barrels/day upgrader for fuel/chemicals.  
  *Where*: Houston, TX (Gulf Coast hub).  
  *When*: 2025-2028 (operational by 2028).  
  *Cost*: $10B  
  *Impact*: $1.50/gallon gas ($400B ICE sales), $500B chemicals, co-op fuel anchor.

- **Chicago Co-op Upgrader**  
  *What*: 100K barrels/day upgrader.  
  *Where*: Chicago, IL (Midwest hub).  
  *When*: 2025-2028 (operational by 2028).  
  *Cost*: $10B  
  *Impact*: $3B revenue, Midwest ICE/gas-hybrid fuel ($5B co-op trade), chemical feedstock.

- **Fission Reactors (AP1000 Network) – Phase 1**  
  *What*: 10GW across 7 sites: Houston (2GW), Chicago (2GW), Marcellus (2GW), San Antonio (1GW), Dallas/Fort Worth (1GW), N.C. Research Triangle (1GW), Payette (1GW).  
  *Where*: Houston, TX; Chicago, IL; Marcellus (PA); San Antonio, TX; Dallas/Fort Worth, TX; Raleigh-Durham, NC; Payette, ID/WY.  
  *When*: 2025-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $32B (of $48B total)  
  *Impact*: Powers chemical hubs ($1T), cuts oil demand 10% ($1.5B savings), co-op jobs (6.3M).

- **LNG Terminals (Houston)**  
  *What*: 10B cubic feet/day (two terminals).  
  *Where*: Houston, TX (Gulf Coast).  
  *When*: 2026-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $10B  
  *Impact*: $1.5T exports, global energy pact ($500B), ties Permian/Marcellus gas.

- **Bakken-to-Chicago Gas Pipeline**  
  *What*: 300M cubic feet/day pipeline capturing flared gas.  
  *Where*: Bakken Shale (ND/MT) to Chicago, IL.  
  *When*: 2027-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $5B  
  *Impact*: $1B/year revenue, powers Chicago hub ($3T GDP), supports ICE/gas-hybrids.

- **Gulf Offshore Gas Capture**  
  *What*: 200M cubic feet/day capture systems.  
  *Where*: Gulf of Mexico (off TX/LA coast).  
  *When*: 2027-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $3B  
  *Impact*: $500M/year revenue, integrates with Houston LNG ($1.5T exports), $500B chemicals.

- **Houston/Chicago Upgrader Petrochemical Retrofit**  
  *What*: $5B/year chemical output (10 plants converting byproducts).  
  *Where*: Houston, TX (5 plants); Chicago, IL (5 plants).  
  *When*: 2028-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $5B  
  *Impact*: Scales chemicals to $1.5T, adds $100B co-op revenue, leverages existing upgraders.

- **Coal Mine Methane (CMM) Capture**  
  *What*: 100M cubic feet/day methane capture.  
  *Where*: Appalachia (PA/WV, near Marcellus) and Illinois Basin (IL).  
  *When*: 2028-2029 (operational by 2029).  
  *Cost*: $2B  
  *Impact*: $200M/year revenue, boosts Marcellus/Chicago co-ops ($5B trade), cuts emissions.

