**Self-Reinforcement**: Energy (7.7B cubic feet/day, 15GW) funds shipping ($60B savings), which boosts exports ($3.3T), enabling innovation (hydrogen 20%, thorium/fusion). Co-ops ($1.7T loans) and National Service (500K workers) tie it together.  
**Max Effect**: Early gas/chemical wins (2029) finance trade networks (2033), setting up innovation (2055). CMM and hydrogen close gaps, ensuring resilience.  
**Tweaks Applied**: All suggestions integrated—CMM (#12), retrofit scaled (#11), rail added (#19), hydrogen explicit (#24), fusion accelerated (#27).  

